RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 1 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 93. Starter Allowance Purse 33000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 23 Allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DURANTE sped clear from inside, inched away two then three wide on the turn, spurted away at the top of the lane, widened to the eighth pole and was ridden out to the wire. RIFEY was off slow to begin and trailed early, went five then six wide around the turn, summoned a mild response and bested the others. MR. T'S THIRSTY stumbled a bit at the start, tracked three wide into the turn, moved out and came five wide into the drive and gained the show. INDULGE forwardly placed in the early going three deep then chased outside a rival, went four to five wide on the turn and flattened in the stretch run. BARSABAS brushed the gate, raced up close between foes then chased off the rail, took the turn three then four wide and weakened in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Durante
ENTRY.COMMENT: sped clear, 2-3wide, spurted away, ridden out

ENTRY.NAME: Barsabas
ENTRY.COMMENT: brushed gate, up close between, chased 3-4wide, weakened

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 2 1M Dirt CR: 97. Starter Allowance Purse 21000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $12,500 OR LESS. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 9 Allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ALOHA KITTEN pressed the pace from inside, chased the top pair from inside through the far turn, continued within striking distance into the final eighth, tipped out nearing the sixteenth pole and drove past. INDY'S STAR chased three wide early, raced up close outside the top pair in the middle stages, took over midway around the far turn, cleared at the five-sixteenths pole and showed the way four wide into the lane, drifted out then inward while continuing clear into the final eighth, had the rider lost the whip shortly after crossing that marker and got run down the in late stages. BLOSSOMING brushed from outside then went up to take control three wide into the first turn, set the pace under pressure up the backstretch, relinquished the lead midway around the far turn, chased three wide into the drive and weakened. LUCY L broke in and brushed, trailed four wide around the first turn, moved into range in the middle stages, went three wide into the far turn, lost ground while easing further out and came five wide into the drive and weakened. VANDALIA showed speed from the rail then paused briefly into the first turn, chased along the rail through the second bend while dropping back, eased in the lane and walked off.

ENTRY.NAME: Vandalia
ENTRY.COMMENT: paused into 1st, chased inside, tired, eased

ENTRY.NAME: Aloha Kitten
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed inside, chased, tipped out, came back

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Kenneth L. Ramsey & Sarah K. Ramsey

ENTRY.NAME: Lucy L
ENTRY.OWNER: Horseplayers Racing Club Saratoga West Ortega Jr Alex and Ortega Vincent

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 79. Claiming Purse 16000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 9 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.

CLAIM.OWNER: Campuzano Lorenzo and Talamantes Filiberto G

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CHOLLIMA bumped leaving the gate, went to vie inside pair early, held a short lead over outside rivals two wide into the stretch, shook free past the three-sixteenths pole and drew away. TALKATIVE GAL fractious in the gate, hopped at the start, trailed on the inside into the turn, two wide into the lane, angled out widest and got up for second. ISLAND LIFE vied three deep for command, dueled four wide into the stretch, could not match strides with the winner past the three-sixteenths pole, churned on in the final furlong and saved the show. FLAG SALUTE was fractious in the gate, prominent early then chased the top trio two wide into the turn, angled over to the rail around the bend, failed to find the needed late kick in the final furlong and missed the show honors. AUNT OPAL bumped with inner rival at the start, sent for the front and vied between rivals into and around the turn, failed to keep up at the top of the stretch, drifted out at the three-sixteenths pole and weakened. PER THE HORSE RACING INTEGRITY AND WELFARE UNIT, CHOLLIMA HAS BEEN DQ'D DUE TO A POSITIVE TEST.

ENTRY.NAME: dq-Chollima
ENTRY.OWNER: Belico Racing LLC and Medina Lizbeth
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, vied inside, shook free

ENTRY.NAME: Aunt Opal
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, vied between, drifted out 3/16, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Flag Salute
ENTRY.OWNER: Blue Sky Training Center and Spasiano Alexander J

ENTRY.NAME: Talkative Gal
ENTRY.COMMENT: fractious, hopped, inside-2wide, angled out, up for 2nd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 4 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 83. Starter Allowance Purse 33000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 9 Allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BIG HAT WILLIE broke a step slow then lost his path early, stalked three deep between rivals, got boxed in at the seven-sixteenths pole, split rivals with a furlong to go and drove clear late. THE BULLION BOMBER (IRE) set the pace under pressure, led two wide around the turn then clear three wide into the lane, remained unchallenged approaching the sixteenth pole but got run down late. TAHOE SECRETS stalked four deep to the turn, five wide into the lane, chased through the final furlong but could not summon the needed late kick while earning the show honors. CATHEDRAL LIGHT broke a step slow, chased between rivals into the turn, two wide leaving the bend, kept on through the lane and got edged for third. BUCK OWENS pressed the pace from outside, chased the leader four wide into the lane and was outfinished in the late stages. LITTLEBROTHERJOEY raced up close on the inside, saved ground through the turn and tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Littlebrotherjoey
ENTRY.OWNER: Medina Lizbeth and Pineda Milton G

ENTRY.NAME: The Bullion Bomber (IRE)
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pressured pace, 2-3wide, cleared, yield late

ENTRY.NAME: Big Hat Willie
ENTRY.OWNER: Altamira Racing Stable and Kagele Tom
ENTRY.COMMENT: step slow, lost path, stalked 3deep, boxed in 7/16

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 5 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 83. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 47000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $20,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Other Than Maiden, Claiming Or Starter Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KO OLINA sped clear to take control, showed the way two then three wide on the turn, drifted out in upper stretch, drifted inward nearing the eighth pole and remained clear to the wire. BIG NOVEL was off slow from inside, stalked the pacesetter along the inside, roused two wide into the lane, altered out from behind the leader approaching the eighth pole, could not summon the needed late kick but proved second best. EVERLYS GIRL stalked three deep into the turn, went four then five wide around the bend and finished evenly. FEELING GRAZEFUL got bumped leaving the gate, was closest in pursuit three wide into the turn, spun four wide into the drive and flattened in the final furlong. FRIED ASPARAGUS broke in and bumped rival then tossed head, raced in range widest into the turn, angled down to the three path around the bend before steering back out into the lane and weakened in the stretch run.

ENTRY.COMMENT: off slow, stalked inside-2wide, altered midstr, 2nd best

ENTRY.OWNER: Guernsey Jade H and Osborne Candice J

ENTRY.COMMENT: speed 2-3wide, drifted out/in str, stayed clear

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 6 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 88. Claiming Purse 16000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 9 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: VICENTE'S SHADOW trailed three wide into the turn, angled out and came five wide into the stretch, unleashed a rally through the lane and inhaled BIG CHEDDAR late. BIG CHEDDAR sprinted clear early, led two to three wide into the stretch, remained clear into the final sixteenth and was run down by the winner late. SPEEDING STYLE got shuffled back at the start, chased out of range four to five wide on the turn, rallied in the final furlong but lacked the needed late punch to get by the top pair. QUICK INTRO coaxed along chasing outside rivals early, lost ground three then four wide on the turn, angled into the two path leaving the bend and summoned a mild rally to round out the superfecta. SCRATCHY APACHE was hard to load prior to the start, broke a step slow, sat off the pace on the inside, cut the corner into the stretch and failed to menace. BIG CREEK chased two wide into the turn, remained off the rail into the lane, split foes in a tight spot at the sixteenth pole and could not threaten. DEBT MONGER forwardly placed outside a rival, went four wide around the bend and flattened in the drive. TIME TO ZOOM brushed the gate, raced up close early, drifted out a bit at the seven-sixteenths pole, entered the lane three wide and weakened.

ENTRY.NAME: Big Creek
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased inside, 2-3wide, split foes 1/16, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Scratchy Apache
ENTRY.COMMENT: hard to load, step slow, inside, no menace

ENTRY.NAME: Time to Zoom
ENTRY.OWNER: Ortega, Jr., Alex and Ortega, Vincent
ENTRY.COMMENT: brushed gate, up close, drifted bit 7/16, 3wide into str,weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Speeding Style
ENTRY.OWNER: Ortega, Jr., Alex and Ortega, Vincent

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 82. Maiden Claiming Purse 29000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STOP AND A TRES vied three deep between rivals to the stretch, dueled outside BURTON WAY down the lane and dug in the final sixteenth to draw clear. BURTON WAY vied between rivals into and around the bend, fought inside STOP AND A TRES through the stretch run and got outkicked in deep stretch. RAHM took a slight hop at the start, chased five wide into the turn, six wide into the lane, summoned a mild rally and got up for the show. CHARLIE'S GHOST vied for the lead inside several rivals to the stretch, could not keep up at the top of the lane and got edged for the show. SNAPP DADDY was off a bit slow from inside, stalked next to the fence into the turn, drifted five wide around the bend and could not rally. BRAZEN BULL got bumped on both sides leaving the gate, bumped with inner rival while vying five deep, four deep for command and weakened in midstretch. FINDING LOVE got bumped hard from inside at the start, tracked four then three wide on the turn and failed to menace. TACOMA SOUND broke out and bumped rival then bumped again early, vied four deep up the backstretch, failed to keep up and drifted out around the bend and had little left in the drive.

ENTRY.COMMENT: bit slow, stalked inside, drifted 5wide turn, no rally

ENTRY.COMMENT: vied 3deep between, dueled, dug in late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 8 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 89. Starter Allowance Purse 16000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $6,250 OR LESS. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 9 Allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FACTS MATTER raced up close outside the top pair, exited the bend five wide, took over at the three-sixteenths pole, cleared inner rival with a furlong remaining and held over the late charge from the runner-up. J T'S WATCH got bumped and lost his path at the start, chased outside a rival off the pace, went two wide into the lane, tipped out midstretch and was gaining outside the winner to the wire. WHISKY MY GOD (ARG) bumped outer rival at the start, took control from inside then got pressure by PEDRO PEREZ up the backstretch, cleared that rival past the five-sixteenths pole and showed the way two wide into the drive, was overtaken by the winner at the three-sixteenths pole and kept on to hold the show. PEDRO PEREZ pressed the pace from outside, lost touch with the leader past the five-sixteenths pole, entered the lane four wide and churned on for a minor award. DR. TROUTMAN broke a step slow then was coaxed into range outside the top trio, drifted out and came seven wide into the lane and kept to his task but needed to find more late. AROUND THE DIAL got bumped on both sides leaving the gate, chased from off the pace on the inside then two wide into the lane and was not a factor. PERFECTO AMOR stumbled badly at the start, raced three deep at the back into the turn, spun five wide into the lane and was not a factor. PER RULING FROM HIWU, FACTS MATTER WAS DISQUALIFIED FOR POSITIVE TEST.

ENTRY.NAME: Whisky My God (ARG)
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, pace inside-2wide, cleared, faltered

ENTRY.NAME: Around the Dial
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped both sides, inside-2wide, no factor

ENTRY.NAME: Pedro Perez
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed outside, 4wide into stretch, no match

ENTRY.NAME: dq-Facts Matter
ENTRY.COMMENT: up close 3deep, 5wide into lane, cleared, held
